  "Angles that differ by exactly 90 degrees": "",
  "Angles that add up to 360 degrees": "",
  "Angles that are complementary": "",
  "Coterminal angles are angles that, when drawn in standard position, share the same terminal side. They differ by multiples of 360 degrees (or 2pi radians), such as 30 degrees and 390 degrees.": "",
